Brazilian Stock Movers: Itau, Vale Decline; Localiza Advances

-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 
2011-03-10T21:33:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-10/brazilian-stock-movers-cia-siderurgica-itau-unibanco-vale.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:15 p.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index fell 1.8 percent to 66,040.66.  Banks tumbled after the central bank signaled it might take
further measures to curb credit in order to contain inflation.  Itau Unibanco Holding SA (ITUB4)  (ITUB4 BS), Latin America’s biggest
bank by market value, fell 3.8 percent to 34.82 reais.  Banco
Bradesco SA (BBDC4)  (BBDC4 BS) declined 3.7 percent to 30.22 reais.    Localiza Rent a Car SA (RENT3)  (RENT3 BS) gained 0.6 percent to
23.58 reais. About 200 million reais ($120.3 million) of bonds
due 2014 issued by the car-rental company were raised to Baa3
from Ba1 at Moody’s Investors Service.    MPX Energia SA (MPXE3)  (MPXE3 BS) fell 5.5 percent to 37.01 reais.
The energy company controlled by Brazilian billionaire Eike Batista plans to sell as much as 1.3 billion reais in three-year
convertible bonds to finance coal and natural-gas projects in
Colombia and  Brazil , according to a regulatory filing.    Vale SA (VALE3)  (VALE5 BS) dropped 3.3 percent to 46.06 reais.  China ’s imports of iron-ore tumbled 29 percent last month from
January, according to the country’s General Administration of
Customs. China is Vale’s top export market.  To contact the reporter on this story:
